  sugar: 10 g
  protein: 58 g
  fiber: 11 g
  sodium: 2150 mg
cuisine: Mexican
---

Wash and dry produce. Quarter @lime{1}. Core, deseed, and dice @long green pepper{1}(core, deseeded, and diced). Drain and rinse @black beans{1}.

In a small #bowl{}, combine @sour cream{3%tablespoon} with a big squeeze of lime juice to taste. Stir in @water{1%tsp} 1 tsp at a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{1%tsp} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add @ground turkey{10%ounce}; season with salt and pepper. Cook, breaking up meat into pieces, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}. Turn off heat; transfer to a medium bowl.

> Ground Turkey is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in a large pan over medium-high heat. Add green pepper and cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{3-4%minutes}.

Add beans and @Tex-Mex paste{1}; season with salt and pepper. Cook until beans are warmed through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Turn off heat. Transfer to a medium bowl. Wash out pan.

> Use pan used for beef or turkey here.

Once green pepper and beans are done, transfer to bowl with beef or turkey and stir to combine.

Place @flour tortillas{2} on a clean work surface; evenly top one half of each tortilla with @Mexican cheese blend{1%cup}. Top with filling, then sprinkle with @Monterey Jack cheese{¼%cup}. Fold tortillas in half to create quesadillas.

Melt @butter{1%tablespoon} in pan used for filling over medium-high heat. (For 4 servings, you may need to work in batches, using 1 TBSP butter for each batch.) Add quesadillas; cook until tortillas are golden brown and cheese melts, ~{2-4%minutes} per side.

Cut quesadillas into thirds and divide between plates. Drizzle with lime crema and @hot sauce{1%tsp} to taste. Serve.